ENTRY            A0108   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0108001   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 11         29
TITLE      Low-energy fission investigated in reactions of
           750 A*MeV 238U-ions on 208Pb
               II: Isotopic distributions
AUTHOR     (C.Donzaud,S.Czajkowski,P.Armbruster,M.Bernas,
           C.Bockstiegel,Ph.Dessagne,H.Geissel,E.Hanelt, A.Heinz,
           C.Kozhuharov,Ch.Miehe,G.Munzenberg, M.Pfiitzner,
           W.Schwab,C.Stephan,K.Summerer, L.Tassan-Got,B.Voss)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,1,407,1998)
INSTITUTE  (2FR PAR,2GERGSI,2FR GRA,2FR STR,2GERTHD,3POLWWA)
FACILITY   (OLMS,2GERGSI)
           (SYNCY,2GERGSI)
DETECTOR   (PS) FRS spectrometer
INC-SOURCE A beam of 2. x 10**5 238U ions/s accelerated up to
           750 A x MeV by the heavy-ion synchrotron SIS
SAMPLE     1.26 g/cm2 Pb target located at the entrance focus of
           the fragment separator FRS.
METHOD     (OLMS,TOF)
ADD-RES    Mean total number of the evaporated neutrons for
           symmetric and asymmetric modes of fission.
           Total kinetic energy distribution.
           Odd-Even effects.
HISTORY    (20000718C)
           (20010614A) Remarks of V.Mclane are included.
           (20010615U) Last checking has been done.
           (20180117A) SD: Entry updated. INC-SOURCE, SAMPLE,
           DETECTOR were added. Subents 002-244 were merged;
           data were re-digitized. Corrections in all Subents.
           En=178500 MeV -> 750 MeV/A in COMMON section.
           (20260126A) SD: Small corrections in several Subents.
ENDBIB              29
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV/A
    750.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           36
SUBENT        A0108002   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  4          7
REACTION   (82-PB-0(92-U-238,F),,SIG)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The uncertainty of the measurement of the
           beam intensity (7%)
           (ERR-T) Total error
STATUS     (TABLE,,C.Donzaud+,J,EPJ/A,1,407,1998) Text on p. 416
HISTORY    (20180117U) SD: ERR-ANALYS update. STATUS added.
           (20260126U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB               7
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 3          1
DATA       ERR-T      ERR-1
B          B          PER-CENT
        2.2      0.2      7.
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           15
SUBENT        A0108003   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  4         14
REACTION   (82-PB-0(92-U-238,F)ELEM/MASS,,SIG)
            Only cross sections with uncertainties smaller
            than 50% are considered.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The uncertainty of the measurement of the
           beam intensity (7%)
           (ERR-2) The uncertainty of around 10% on transmission
           absolute values is a possible source of systematic
           error on cross sections values.
           (ERR-T) Total error given on fig.7 when it is greater
            than the size of the point on fig.
